[ProMED-mail has previously commented on the outbreak in Wajir, and we
still presume that the diagnosis is correct although an outbreak of a
haemorrhagic fever may not be completely ruled out with regard to the
symptoms of bleeding reported in the dispatch. As pointed out in an earlier
comment, leishmaniasis is one of the infections that emerge with HIV and it
is important to know the proportion of HIV-positives among the patients
reported with leishmaniasis. - Mod.EP
